  "text": "The patient lies in supine position, while the practitioner holds the affected limb by the forearm and hand (Fig. 6 ). The practitioner then places his heel in the axilla of the affected shoulder, acting as a fulcrum while the arm is adducted, initiating reduction. [CITATION_1] ",
